description: {"blocks":[{"key":"2u2k2","text":"Reverse Transcribe \u0026 Tagment (RT\u0026Tag) is a method that capitalizes on the ability of the Tn5 transposase to tagment RNA-cDNA hybrids. RT\u0026Tag bypasses immunoprecipitation and instead uses antibodies to tether a protein A-Tn5 transposase fusion protein in situ. By performing localized reverse transcription and tagmentation, one can capture RNAs associated with an epitope of interest within intact nuclei. With RT\u0026Tag, one can generate sequencing libraries using only 100,000 Drosophila cells and require only 8 million sequencing reads per sample.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":251,"length":8}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3qro0","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3csi2","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"dlf75","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"DD8AEC50441311ED9F30511A7BA3A7CB","height":984,"id":299662,"is_video":false,"legend":"","mime":"image/png","original_name":"Screen Shot 2022-10-04 at 11.31.25 AM.png","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jewsbbx2p.jpg","source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jewqbbx2p.jpg","type":1,"webp_placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jewrbbx2p.webp","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/jewpbbx2p.webp","width":550}}}}
